item.title: Wasnt quite sure about this one
item.dc:creator: @exe626 exe626
item.description:
@exe626 wrote:

I’ve used that render before, but even if your using gimp, you can do better - gimps not too much difficult to work with. What are those things flying around? Flaming lifesavers?? =D
Somethings to improve on:
Text
-Your text is not only sloppy, its too ‘wavy’(for the lack of other terms).
And if you want it to be black, and readable, I would suggest not putting it there, with the way this goes I would suggest it being at an angle, to follow the flow and remain readable.

Render
-Your render is just sitting there, it seems like somebody dropped this devilish person into heaven to see how well he would stick out, it just doesn’t fit. Something alot of newer people do is feather the outside of the render in different areas on multiple layers to make some seem to fade away and some to come out closer(creating depth).

Background
-No seriously, are those flaming life savers?
